As explained in the [Apache POI Javadocs](https://poi.apache.org/apidocs/org/apache/poi/ss/usermodel/Cell.html#setCellType%28int%29), you *should not* use `cell.setCellType(Cell.CELL_TYPE_STRING)` to get the string value of a numeric cell, as you&#39;ll loose all the formatting

Instead, as the [javadocs explain](https://poi.apache.org/apidocs/org/apache/poi/ss/usermodel/Cell.html#setCellType%28int%29), you should use [DataFormatter](http://poi.apache.org/apidocs/org/apache/poi/ss/usermodel/DataFormatter.html)

What DataFormatter does is take the floating point value representing the cell is stored in the file, along with the formatting rules applied to it, and returns you a string that look like it the cell does in Excel.

So, if you&#39;re after a String of the cell, looking much as you had it looking in Excel, just do:

     // Create a formatter, do this once
