It means that Hibernate has loaded metadata from different class rather than from a class of an object you are trying to save. Please, check if there are only one class OHLCV in the classpath of your application, because example you provided works well.

instead of downgrading, I rebuild my Entity to use ```@IdClass```

Continuing on the given example, you can remove the @Embeddable and @EmbeddedId annotations. Then you should add on class level for your ```OHLCV``` the following annotation: 

```
javax.persistence.@IdClass(OHLCVKey.class)
```
copy the variables from the ```OHLCVKey``` class to your ```OHLCV``` class and add the following annotation **to each of them!** 

```@Id``` 

Then remove the column-annotations from the key-class.
Don&#39;t forget that each class needs an Equal&#39;s and hashCode implementation!

A small custom example: 
```
@Entity
@Table(name = &quot;MY_TABLE&quot;)
@IdClass(ExampleCompositeKey.class)
public class Example {
    
    @Id
    @Column(name = &quot;COLUMN_ONE&quot;)
    private String something;
    
    @Id
    @Column(name = &quot;COLUMN_TWO&quot;)
    private String somethingElse;
    
    @Column(name = &quot;COLUMN_THREE&quot;)
    private String regularColumn;
    
    // GETTER&#39;s and SETTER&#39;s here...
    
    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object o) {
        if (this == o) return true;
        if (!(o instanceof Example)) return false;
        Example example = (Example) o;
        return Objects.equals(something, example.something)
                &amp;&amp; Objects.equals(somethingElse, example.somethingElse)
                &amp;&amp; Objects.equals(regularColumn, example.regularColumn);
    }

    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return Objects.hash(something, somethingElse, regularColumn);
    }
}
```
```
public class ExampleCompositeKey implements Serializable {

    private String something;
    private String somethingElse;

    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object o) {
        if (this == o) return true;
        if (!(o instanceof ExampleCompositeKey)) return false;
        ExampleCompositeKey that = (ExampleCompositeKey) o;
        return Objects.equals(something, that.something)
                &amp;&amp; Objects.equals(somethingElse, that.somethingElse);
    }

    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return Objects.hash(something, somethingElse);
    }
}
```

